      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Ossuary has inner ledge on three sides, low feet, and flat sliding lid. Ornamentation, on each of four sides, consists of a frame of narrow, gouged lines, perhaps representing an ashlar. The inscribed phrase appears once each on the chest's front and right sides, with a difference in spelling of the final letter of the word "builder." The name סמון is a transliteration of the Greek form of שמעון. The ossuary contains, along with the remains of a man and a woman, the bone of a dog, possibly the result of carelessness in the process of ossilegium or in sealing the tomb and loculus.</p>
         </div>
